main event: A resident of Kenosha, Wisconsin saw a slightly shining light moving in a direct line from north to south at an altitude of 10,000 to 15,000 feet on May 17, 1950.
interesting points: The light stopped on the southeast horizon and then started moving in a southeasterly direction.
The light moved slowly and then continued on its way until it disappeared from sight.
The weather was slightly cloudy with a very slight wind from the northeast at 3-4 miles per hour.
The witness was a 43-year-old man named Turningure.
witnesses: a 43-year-old man named Turningure and a friend
